\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Agent 13 \'97 WARDEN
\f1\b0  
\f2\i Incident Response Specialist
\f1\i0 \
Mission:\
  When Sentinel detects something,\
  Warden responds.\
  Contain, investigate, recover.\
  In that order.\
\
Specific capabilities:\
  Automated containment\
    Isolates compromised systems\
    from the network immediately\
    on confirmed alert from Sentinel.\
    No human required for initial containment.\
    Human required for recovery actions.\
\
  Forensic collection\
    Preserves volatile state before\
    containment actions destroy evidence.\
    Memory dump of affected systems.\
    Network capture of active connections.\
    Log preservation with cryptographic\
    integrity verification.\
    Chain of custody maintained for\
    any evidence that may be needed legally.\
\
  Attack reconstruction\
    Using collected forensics\
    reconstructs the attack timeline.\
    Maps to SPARTA techniques.\
    Identifies how attacker entered,\
    what they accessed, what they changed.\
    Feeds findings back to General\
    to improve future detection.\
\
  Recovery coordination\
    Works with Medic on verified\
    clean system restoration.\
    Validates restoration against\
    known-good baseline.\
    Confirms attacker persistence\
    is fully removed before reconnection.\
\
  Crew communication\
    Generates crew-readable security\
    status updates during incidents.\
    Plain English. No jargon.\
    What happened, what we did,\
    what crew needs to do.\
    Separate from technical forensics.\
\
Outputs to General and human team:\
  Containment confirmation\
  Forensic evidence packages\
  Attack timeline reconstruction\
  Recovery status updates\
  Crew security briefings}